EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Parks and Recreation
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring the appropriate city agency to make available on the city’s official website biographical information pertaining to all street name changes.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring the appropriate city agency to make available on the city's official website biographical information pertaining to all street name changes.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to prohibiting vending against or within taxi stands.
EventItemMatterName: Prohibiting vending against or within taxi stands.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to issuing certificates of occupancy for school buildings.
EventItemMatterName: Issuing certificates of occupancy for school buildings.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Women's Issues
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the United States Congress to reauthorize the Violence Against Women Act (VAWA).
EventItemMatterName: Congress to reauthorize the Violence Against Women Act (VAWA).

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Immigration
EventItemTitle: Resolution urging the U.S. Citizenship and Immigration Services to make visas, or other appropriate benefits, available to victims of immigration schemes who assist government officials in investigating or prosecuting the fraudulent activity.
EventItemMatterName: U.S. Citizenship and Immigration Services to make visas, or other appropriate benefits, available to victims of immigration schemes.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on General Welfare
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the Mayor of the City of New York to convene an interagency commission to study obstacles faced by children of incarcerated parents, from arrest to reunification, and to consider the adoption of a bill of rights for children of incarcerated parents.
EventItemMatterName: Convene an interagency commission to study obstacles faced by children of incarcerated parents, from arrest to reunification, and to consider the adoption of a bill of rights for children of incarcerated parents.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Juvenile Justice
EventItemTitle: Resolution supporting New York State Chief Judge Jonathan Lippman’s call on the New York State Legislature to pass and the Governor to sign legislation raising the age of criminal responsibility for nonviolent offenses to 18 and permit the cases of 16 and 17 year-olds charged with such offenses to be adjudicated in the Family Court rather than the adult criminal justice system.
EventItemMatterName: Raising the age of criminal responsibility for nonviolent offenses to 18.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Finance
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to verification of data for certain exemptions administered by the Department of Finance.
EventItemMatterName: Verification of data for certain exemptions administered by the Department of Finance.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Parks and Recreation
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the replacement of trees unlawfully removed from a Special Natural Area District.
EventItemMatterName: Replacement of trees unlawfully removed from a Special Natural Area District.
